      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<p><style>[data-colorid=rbb9ig13y0]{color:#3d90b3} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=rbb9ig13y0]{color:#4c9fc2}[data-colorid=trqaxcwqbj]{color:#3d90b3} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=trqaxcwqbj]{color:#4c9fc2}[data-colorid=l42b9htzbf]{color:#3d90b3} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=l42b9htzbf]{color:#4c9fc2}[data-colorid=j0tx0etpc8]{color:#3d90b3} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=j0tx0etpc8]{color:#4c9fc2}</style><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\"><br /><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542219300/RenderMan_Lama_Yellow.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330546315&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542219300/RenderMan_Lama_Yellow.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330546315&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"542219315\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderMan_Lama_Yellow.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"542219300\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"e1be81b1-e343-4c8b-b331-f328f7ea0692\" data-media-type=\"file\" /></span><br /><br /><br />LamaAdd is simply adding two materials together, controlled by individual weights.</span></p><div class=\"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-warning conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"16d4ef89-79c5-4eb9-8954-ecfaa4e75b55\" data-macro-name=\"warning\"><span class=\"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-error confluence-information-macro-icon\"> </span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro-body\"><p><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">If both weights add up to more than 1.0, you might be reflecting more light than is received by the surface. This may prevent the render from converging normally as it breaks energy conservation!</span></p></div></div><p><span data-colorid=\"rbb9ig13y0\">Material 1</span></p><p><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">This is the first material to mix</span></p><p><span data-colorid=\"l42b9htzbf\">Material 2</span></p><p><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">The second material to be mixed.</span></p><p><span data-colorid=\"trqaxcwqbj\">Weight 1</span></p><p><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">The mixed value of material 1.&nbsp; You can also use a map here to control the value</span></p><p><span data-colorid=\"j0tx0etpc8\">Weight 2</span></p><p><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">The mixed value of material 2.&nbsp; You can also use a map here to control the value</span></p><p><br /></p>"
